# Cursor Rules for The Useless App Suite

## Project Structure

- Follow the repo structure defined in user rules strictly
- Main hub page: `index.html` (root directory)
- All app pages go under `/frontend` (one file per app)
- Shared resources: `frontend/shared.css` and `frontend/shared.js`
- Boot scripts in `/boot`
- Documentation in `/docs`
- Configs in `/configs`

## Code Style

- Use ES6+ JavaScript
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Shared styles in `frontend/shared.css`
- Shared utilities in `frontend/shared.js`
- Each app page is a standalone HTML file
- Follow STYLE_GUIDE.md for conventions

## File Organization

- **Main Hub:** `index.html` - Entry point with app cards
- **App Pages:** `frontend/[app-name].html` - One file per app
  - `frontend/progress.html` - Progress Simulator
  - `frontend/currency.html` - Currency Converter
  - `frontend/hold.html` - Hold On Game
  - `frontend/weather.html` - Nihilist Weather
  - `frontend/clock.html` - Manual Clock
  - `frontend/pet-rock.html` - Digital Pet Rock
  - `frontend/ego-inflator.html` - Ego Inflator
  - `frontend/bubble-wrap.html` - Virtual Bubble Wrap
  - `frontend/typing-speedster.html` - Typing Speedster
  - `frontend/un-calculator.html` - Un-Calculator
  - `frontend/dusting.html` - Digital Dusting
  - `frontend/bureaucracy-snake.html` - Bureaucracy Snake
  - `frontend/minesweeper.html` - Minesweeper (Bureaucratic)
  - `frontend/minesweeper-active.html` - Minesweeper (Regular)
  - `frontend/solitaire.html` - Solitaire Protocol
  - `frontend/weeb-shop.html` - Weeb Shop
- **Shared:** `frontend/shared.css` and `frontend/shared.js`

## Navigation

- Use standard HTML links (`<a>` tags) for navigation
- Each app page includes a "Back to Hub" button linking to `../index.html`
- Back button is hidden on mobile (â‰¤768px) - users can use browser back button
- No JavaScript-based routing (multi-page architecture)

## Documentation

- **ALWAYS update `CHANGELOG.md` in root directory** when making any changes
- Changelog format: Use [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) format
- Document all changes in appropriate sections: Added, Changed, Fixed, Removed
- Always update PLANNING.md when making architectural changes
- Keep README.md files current
- Update ARCHITECTURE.md when structure changes

## Changelog System

- **Root CHANGELOG.md** is the primary changelog file
- Update it immediately after making any changes
- Use semantic versioning for version numbers
- Document changes in reverse chronological order (newest first)
- Include detailed descriptions of what was added/changed/fixed
- Be specific about features, UI changes, bug fixes, and improvements

## Firebase

- Use anonymous authentication only
- Firestore for leaderboard data (Hold On app)
- Configuration via environment variables
- Firebase config can be injected via global variables

## Local Storage

- Use `Storage` utility from `shared.js` for all localStorage operations
- All keys prefixed with `useless-suite-` for namespacing
- Persist user preferences and app state

## Development

- Test locally before committing
- Run `npm run check` for code quality checks
- Keep app pages modular and independent
- Each app should be self-contained but can use shared resources
- **Update CHANGELOG.md after every change**

## Netlify Deployment

- Main entry point: `index.html` (root)
- Publish directory: `.` (root)
- All app pages accessible via `frontend/[app-name].html`
- `_redirects` file handles routing fallbacks

## Code Quality

- Node.js 16+ and npm 8+ required for linting
- Run `npm install` to set up development tools
- Use `npm run check` for automated quality checks
- Follow accessibility guidelines (WCAG 2AA)
